Hypo Alpe to Report 2010 Loss of 1 Billion Euros, Standard Says

-- B y   Z o e   S c h n e e w e i s s
-- 
2011-03-23T17:23:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/hypo-alpe-to-report-2010-loss-of-1-billion-euros-standard-says.html
Hypo Alpe-Adria-Bank International
AG, the lender nationalized by  Austria  in 2009, will report a
2010 loss of more than 1 billion euros ($1.4 billion) and bad
debts of about 1.3 billion euros, Der Standard newspaper
reported, citing unidentified people among the bank’s owners.   In addition to the bank’s Austrian and Italian units, which
are being offered for sale, Hypo Alpe has also has hired a Swiss
investment bank to manage its sale of aluminum company Aluflex
in  Croatia , the paper said.     Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
